Preheat oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Place chicken and potatoes in a large baking dish. Season generously with salt and white pepper. In a bowl, stir together garlic, olive oil, and lemon juice. Pour over chicken and potatoes. Cover dish with foil. Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes. Remove foil, increase heat to 475 degrees F (245 degrees C), and cook until chicken and potatoes are golden, about 30 minutes.